-- European Carbon Permits Advance for First Time in Four Days
-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 2012-10-04T13:19:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-04/european-carbon-permits-advance-for-first-time-in-four-days.html
 European Union carbon permits rose
for the first time in four days.  EU allowances for December advanced as much as 4.7 percent,
or 36 cents, to 7.95 euros a metric ton on the ICE Futures
Europe exchange in  London  and were at 7.92 euros as of 2:16 p.m.
local time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Graham in London at 
 rgraham13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
